After several protests to seek for his release, the leader of Islamic Movement in Nigeria (IMN), Sheikh Ibraheem El-Zakzaky was on Monday granted leave to travel abroad for medical attention by the Kaduna State High Court. The court in granting the leave said Zakzaky and his wife are to go on the medical leave under the supervision or the state. was a favourable judgement, which is long overdue. Meanwhile, Counsel to the state government and Director of Public Prosecution, Dari Bayero said they may be appealing the ruling. Members of IMN recently clashed with police in Abuja, resulting to the death of an officer and innocent Nigerians.